font-weight:bold">amily friendly policies and practice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">s</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Family considerations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, particularly caring for young children, can often coincide with a critical stage for academic career development and is a key challenge for women as primary carers.  A lack of flexible working provision, long hours culture and difficulty in achieving a b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">alance between home/family and working lives can lead to many women leaving academic altogether.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">University of Cambridge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">introduced </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a number of measures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to support staff,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">particularly women, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">including:</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Provision of a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Returning Carers Fund</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to support those returning from a period of extended leave (including maternity leave) to get research back on track </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Flexible working policies including part time, job share and condensed hours.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Maternity leave</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> provision</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> above the minimum legal requireme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nt</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Payment for Keeping in Touch days (sector best practice)</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Additional Paternity leave (introduced in 2011)</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Revision of criteria for Senior Academic Promotions to promote gender equality </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font